The paper discusses probabilistic programming and deep probabilistic programming languages, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The focus is on stochastic variational inference algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses program analysis and verification, which are related to software engineering (cs.SE) and control systems (cs.SY).
